    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>If your're looking for a framework for managing zsh configuration, <a href="http://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh">oh-my-zsh</a> is your thing. It supports auto update, auto completion, git integration, very cool <a href="http://wiki.github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/themes">themes</a> and more. You can install it with cloning the repo or via simple command:</p>


<p>&#13;</p>

<blockquote>&#13;
<p>wget http://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/raw/master/tools /install.sh -O - | sh</p>&#13;
</blockquote>


<p>&#13;</p>

